    <note type="biography">
        <p>Barrister and expert on beekeeping. Son of James Lewis Knight Bruce (<hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>). Admitted at Lincoln’s Inn, 1842. A governor of Christ’s Hospital, London. Justice of the peace for Surrey and Middlesex. Resident at Heathfield, Keston, Kent, in the 1850s; friend of CD’s. Succeeded to the family estate of Roehampton Priory, Surrey, in 1866.</p></note>
